<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="130" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Nelson</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 63.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-05-19"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 19, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatches to 124 inclusive have been
                            received.</p>
                        <p>I have to express my cordial approval of your course in the pending
                            controversy between Chili and Bolivia, which I trust is still within the
                            reach of a peaceful and honorable settlement.</p>
                        <p>The Senate having by resolution called for information on the subject, a
                            copy of your No. 123 and of its enclosures has been communicated to that
                            body by the President.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas H. Nelson</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">,</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>